Subject: Re: [VB] Copper or steel brakelines?

On Thu, 7 Nov 2002, FAUTLEY, Paul (Gillingham) wrote:

> I can get complete brakeline kits easily in the UK, but some companies sell
> them with copper lines and others sell them with steel.  I am not going to
> get a true answer if I ask the companies and I expect other people have
> replaced their lines before.

I've never heard of a modern car having brake lines made of copper!
Perhaps some antiques.  Copper tends to work-harden with vibration rather
quickly, so I'd not want to use it.  Stick with steel with an appropriate
anti-corrosion coating if you are worried about rust.

George Lyle
